reviewText:
This game is all about doging various objects with mouse or keyboard. If you like that kind of games than this is maybe for you but I don't recommend it.

Pros:
many levels
difficult
co-operative
Cons:
monotone
background music is somewhat boring
no effects at all
ugly graphics (this kind of graphics is used in pre 90s). I personally don't care much for graphics if gameplay surpass it but here is not that case
Verdict: another unity crap. Hide it or delete.

Cheers!

reviewText:
Reminds me that old test *Fighter pilot challenge* where you had to dodge blue squares as long as you can. Here we can find the same idea but in a more playable form, you have like 7 different modes + impossible mod (which i still have to unlock so cant say anything about that yet), each of them has its own dodge mechanics, it's a nice game to improve mouse controls and mutlitasking.

+Different mods
+Each mode has like 30 difficulty levels
+You can play together with your friend using keyboard
+Pretty time consuming if you decide to unlock impossible mode, cus you have to grind up some coins and unlock all the previous modes
+Improves time of reaction and multitasking skills + peripheral vision
+Low price is obvious plus
-I accidentally bought some pretty expensive *bonuses* when i went to the shop, i think it should have at least some accept button, not just instabuy when you click on it, and you cant revert the sell
